The expected output is 29, however, based on your current Tundra source cod
code, you are adding "2" to a string (because total from item.total appears
appears as a String), not a number. 

You can fix this by converting the strings into numbers before performing a
arithmetic operations using `parseNumber` function. The updated program sho
should look like:

```tundra
def chooseCurrent(groups) {
  return groups[0].items[0];
}

val groups = [
  {
    name: "archive",
    items: [
      { total: "11" }
    ]
  },
  {
    name: "current",
    items: [
      { total: "27" }
    ]
  }
];

val item = chooseCurrent(groups);
val total = parseNumber(item.total) + 2;

print(total);
```
